reviews.review_text: Totally recommended. Last year they prepared my babys 1 year old cake. They are very helpful and accommodating. Food

Recommended to try this place! The dessert tastes amazing. I m not a big fan of sugary sweets, and Minus Cake got the sweetness right!   The cake is fluffy with a creamy mousse texture that melts in the mouth.

I really liked. A nice little place. The service is excellent and we tasted very good desserts. The desserts are not too sweet, they are just right. A varied choice: some combinations are available (bubble cake and drink) but you can also make your own combination. I tried number 7 and the mix of flavors was well thought out!  I would like to go back to try other flavors.

I got the Rose Oolong Peach Cake + Honeycomb Dalgona Latte and my friend got the Vanilla Strawberry Shortcake + Iced Shaken Lychee Black Tea. I would highly recommend the rose peach cake as its something I havent been able to get anywhere else and it tasted divine! The rest was sweet and tasted exactly as expected, especially the strawberry cake and the lychee black tea. Not to make that sound bad, theyre staples in every store for a reason (they never miss)!! Though, not going to lie, wasnt a huge fan of the honeycomb in my dalgona latte as it was too sweet and it was slightly unnerving every time Id encounter its crunchy texture. Still drank it all, but probably wouldnt get it again... Other than that, the decor was nice and clean and the atmosphere was quiet and serene. Also, its a little on the expensive side... so definitely more of an experience than a regular hang-out spot. Hope the employees enjoyed the relaxing morning as it seemed like a slow shift (to be fair we went around brunch time on a Tuesday). Tldr, worth it to try the rose oolong peach cake and experience the fun of the stacking cake cups.
This is so goooooooooood omg! Both combos were delicious and the girl who works at the place is very sweet and helpful. Totally would come again to try all the other combos.
I have to say, the idea of dessert with a bubble tea was just a thought. Now Ive found the real deal. So far I am looking forward to come back and try more of it

Stumbled across this gem on social media and knew we had to try! Wow it did not disappoint!   The cake bubble was seriously the best treat I have had in ages!  So many options to pick from.  Bold strong flavors, creamy moose. The drink was fresh with no artificial flavor. We will be back again!  Just wish they opened sooner!!
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you for coming by Brittaney! Have a great day!

reviews.review_text: Visited this place with my wife on labour day. Nice little shop with cute interior decoration. Service was good. We were a bit confused to see the menu but the staff was explained to us very patiently. Friendly space to hang out with friends and family. Price is reasonable since can enjoy bubble tea and cake at the same time. After tasting the combo we both enjoyed their preset combination. Very unique, creative and aesthetic cup design. The peach cake is my favourite one and they sold out around 3pm today, Im glad to got it. I even ate too fast before I realized to take a picture! Rum cake can taste real rum flavour inside. They hide some raisin inside the cake to bring out the whole texture. Drinks used simple ingredients but very refreshing. I saw they were washing and cut fruits for preparation. I love to see business to use fresh ingredients to highlight their standard in food industry. Very pleasing experience for afternoon snack, will definitely go back again with our children to try their other products!
So fun and delicious!! I love that you can mix and match the drinks and cake. My fav so far is the tiramisu cake with the brown sugar milk tea
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you for coming by! Have a great day!

reviews.review_text: Ordered combo #5. The matcha latte (I asked them to switch corn milk with regular milk for my drink) was very tasty. The cake went perfectly with the drink. Now I understand why they make these two items a combo. I especially love the decorations in the shop. The two ladies at the front desk were very friendly. The containers they used are different from usual bobble tea shop. I can tell they put lot of efforts on everything. More on the pricy side, but worth trying!

Really cute place selling both cold tea and CAKE--all in delicious and unique flavours. Came here yesterday and they were very organized and systematic with Covid rules in place. I got the earl grey cake which was very creamy and not too sweet. I also got the honeycomb dalgona latte and  recommend swirling the foam with milk thoroughly before drinking.
Good combination, dessert and drink, right amount of sweetness. Cute little place. Several options to choose.

Great desserts that were much more then I was expecting. The cake and the drink pairing is such a neat idea, I will definitely be back to try another. I got the seasonal coconut taro ube cake with the mango sago coconut slush. The cake was not too sweet and a perfect light summer cake. The slush paired well as it was not too sweet. My friend and I both got drinks and found them less sweet then we were expecting. For me, I found this a pleasant surprise, but she got a matcha drink and didnt like it as much. So, if you are expecting or wanting a bubble tea level of sweetness, might want to check with the staff about which drinks are sweet. The service was quick (much quicker than bubble tea usually) and I would love to come back and try more flavour combos.

Love the cake+drink combo concept! You can easily devour the delectable   and immediately go for a sip of the  , rinse and repeat   Wonder if someone patented that design because it s just genius and perfect for devouring on the run Had the  cake + lychee iced tea combo with zero sugar and boy this combo was super yum! Cake was sweetened just right and took me back to my childhood when I gorged on Melona treats, but this was better! The Lychee tea had really refreshing fruit bits, this combo is solid! Also tried the   raspberry   cake + hawthorn dates refresher with zero sugar and this was fab too. Now here s my 2 cents on the pricing of the 2 dessert combo - it s pretty fair y all! First we typically pay $7 for a decent cake anyway and also another $7 for a good quality non powdered bbt (you know what I m talking about) and this place is a one-stop shop for you to address your need for a little something nice and sweet. Would I come back again, you bet!

The staff, location, desserts, and atmosphere are so worth it! A unique treat. A mouse like cake of your choice with a yummy drink. Id recommend it for a date night idea, a unique treat, a birthday adventure. And the staff were very friendly to boot!
The fresh mango passion fruit combo was great, but I think the cup design is a bit odd because the straw is kinda stuck and can t stir the drink because of the top round cup.

Perfection each time! I trust no one else to make my cakes. The whole process is done by email, turnaround is quick and professional. I love that they offer delivery and for the quality, the prices are comparable. Thank you Minus!!!

I live in Calgary and wanted to get something as a surprise for my close friend who lives in Vancouver. Found this little bubble tea bake shop online and they exceeded my expectations. They went above and beyond in terms of my delivery and cake request. My friend absolutely loved it. Definitely recommend this place for being so accommodating and sweet. Phenomenal food and service. Thanks so much again!

I m not sure if it s a drink place or a dessert place, but who cares! You can have your cake/bbt and eat it too! Decor is adorable. Cuddle cakes are so soft and delicate, not too sweet, and so delicious. Dessert cups a little on the pricy side, drink + dessert cup = $13-14
Amazing   really good drinks and desserts, fast service and friendly staff - interior is really cute too :)

Very innovative desserts and drinks here. Definitely unique and never seen before. They combine a cake and a drink which you can eat and drink with one hand, perfect for on the go. Not too sweet, seems they tailored it just nicely. Friendly owner, very helpful staff. Street parking is a bit limited. Left: blackcurrant rum raisin cake with lychee slush Mid: chocolate cake with Oreo slush Right: Earl Grey cake with dalgona latte *Edit: owner told me there is more street parking around the side, and a larger parking lot behind their building! Now it is even easier to visit!

We went last week for walk in but realized they don t open for walk in anymore. Everything pre order only. We are their returned customer so didn t check google before we went there. Luckily meet the owner, she let us know she becomes newly mom this year and she wants to make sure cakes made with freshly everyday so she has to make this difficult decision. No maternity leave is cruel for a mom, and she has to take care of her baby plus working everyday. Please be nice to small business owners, they are trying to make things better!!!!

Amazing cakes and drinks! We go every week :) the cake/ drink combo are very cute very IG-able! Delicious cakes. Our fav are chocolate, chocolate caramel, green tea yuzu, and strawberry. Yummy, dif textures inside, not too sweet.  Drinks are very yummy too!! Matcha latte has got loads of matcha powder! Jasmine tea with pearls and milk foam is nice too I like it that this particular tea is unsweetened I think..
One of the best dessert place. Wonderful drinks and all kinds of seasonal cakes. My favorite place.
Gorgeous, delicious, light and not too sweet. So happy. Thank you so much for such a beautiful cake!
Ordered a birthday cake and I am very satisfied :D! The cake is very pretty and it was delivered on time despite I asked for an earlier delivery time at the last minute.
Amazing cake and such lovely people - a perfect local spot. LOVE this bakery.
Been ordering a couple of times! Although a bit pricy but the desserts amaze me every time!!! Will be recommending to all my friends

Late Review We have ordered from Minus Cake Boutique for many festive occasions and our favourite cake is the Jasmine Pearl Lava Cake. It is very creamy with subtle salty and sweet caramelized filling. Unfortunately when I bought the 8inch cake for my mothers birthday November 27, 2021, we discovered the cream in the centre was sour- like sour cream. This made the entire cake taste weird and off-putting . We called the next morning to ask the baker if they knew what happened, although they were not sure and had some hypothesis (maybe they forgot to thin out the cream with fresh cream?) Minus Cake Boutique took ownership of their product and offered to refund (if we bring the cake back) or make a replacement cake. I purchased many times from Minus and a refund was not what I was looking for. I simply wanted to inform them about the quality of their item. There was no way my family could eat another whole  8inch cake (we hate wastage and were determined to carve the sour cream part out of the first cake and make do with what we had) so I suggested making a smaller 6inch one so that we could taste what the cake should taste like. Minus Cake Boutique delivered and we picked up the remade cake and I am grateful and super happy to say, it tasted just the way we remembered it to be. Thank you very much for coming through with excellent customer service. We are very happy and will continue to buy your specialty cakes in the future. Already eyeing another cake for our next festive celebration.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Hello Sigman, Thank you so much for allowing us the chance to rectify this quality issue. We appreciate your patronage to date and look forward to serving you more!

reviews.review_text: The best cake place ever! Ordered a wonderful birthday cake from here and it s just perfect. The flavour is superb and the it looked amazing! I ve tried many cake places and this is the only one I will keep ordering cakes from. The drink with the mini cake is really tasty and unique too, aside from being a little pricey.
Ive been seeing a lot of posts from this cake boutique and decided to try it. I really like the overall decor. The presentation of the cake and  drink is very unique as well!
Absolutely delicious. Much better than a traditional bubble tea. Can tell its made from quality ingredients.
I ordered a mango mousse cake for my birthday and I have to say, this is the best mousse cake in Vancouver!

Wonderful little cafe, I brought my girlfriend here and she enjoyed the cakes and drinks. Definitely a great dating spot if youre looking for something cute. The aesthetic of the place has a great setting for photos. The drinks we had were Earl Grey cake/Rose chocolate & Mango coconut cake/green matcha :)
Cake is so pretty and taste good!! Drink also good too!! Highly recommended~

Drinks: Passion Fruit Grapefruit Refresher and Strawberry Peach Slush Cake: Brown sugar hojicha mochi cake and Earl grey toasted At first I was worried that the drinks was going to be too sweet since there was no option to tweak the sugar/ice level, but they turned out to be just right for my taste, not too sweet. Cakes were yummy too. Again, not too sweet and very good textures.

I place an order for a cake for my nephew for his 1 month. The cake was yummy! Not too sweet and just the perfect flavor. The display box was top notch better than the white soild box. I have order dessert here before and it was good flavor. Will order a customize cake for my sons birthday
Great dessert shop - their combos with tea/milk and cake are super creative. I got the Strawberry combo and no regrets! Place is super clean and they follow all rules during COVID times.

I came across this dessert shop while waiting for sharetea and the line was too long so I gave this place a try as I saw the menu on the window and seemed fresh and interesting.. Having drink and cake at the same time in one cup is definitely a game changer! At first I was a bit skeptical thinking of the combo would be too sweet but surprisingly it wasn t at all. Visited this place 2 times and my favorite combo is the peach slush and peach oreo cake.. the earl grey cake is pretty tasty too. Strawberry milk taste a bit bland but once you stir the strawberry compote well on the bottom..It s pretty amazing..the pear osmanthus drink was bit too light for my taste but my wife loved it..overall great place with friendly staff and great desserts! Def becoming my go to place!

Got a customized cake for my moms bday and she loved both the way it looked and the taste. Also got a chance to go get the cake and drink combo from the Cafe! Both are delicious and have been taking a lot of friends there. I follow their IG, so not surprised to see when they close early because they are selling out everything sometimes.
Great friendly and quick service. Flavour pairings were great, interesting, and satisfying.
Those cups are sooo adorable. PRETTIEST Desserts EVER! Love the earl grey cake and strawberry fresh milk! So Yummy. Highly recommend checking out this cute place and you will be happy you did!
Wide variety of drinks, tasty cakes, and really cute decor. Limited seating, but super cosy!

Definitely worth visiting, the design, combination and flavors are unique and you can choose from a very large variety of unique flavors. I love the Japanese matcha cake and Choco London milk tea most.

What an intriguing cup design - combining cake and drink together! I had combo 1 - vanilla osmanthus lychee cake + osmanthus pear juice with basil seeds. At first, I thought it would be too heavy/sweet. But to my great surprise, the combo was just right! The cake was light, moist and not too sweet. I love the drink, so refreshing. Will go again!
Nice ambience, delicious food and drink. The strawberry milk tastes delicious; the milk is not diluted like such in other bubble tea shops.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you for coming by! Have a great day and hope to see you again

reviews.review_text: Amazing! Amazing! Amazing! The minus cups are completely genius. Both the drink and the cake are perfectly flavoured and not too sweet.

Best place to grab dessert and more. Fabulous idea and excellent presentation of the food. Love the cake and drink combo. Not much space to sit. You may want to get it delivered or grab it and enjoy in your car.
Lovely cakes pair perfectly with their bubble tea.

Cake was tasty and right level of sweetness. Also it was aesthetically pleasing as well. The cafe interior was also very cute. Would be a nice place to hangout post pandemic.
Had a great time here. Deliciously moist cakes and hand crafted bubble tea. I personally believe its better value than share tea next door.
Nice and clean place. Tasty food! I ll definitely come back again !

I have nothing but good things to say! Kind staff. I have boughten two cakes from here as birthday gifts for others and heard nothing but raving reviews back. Really cute interior.
The cake is really good and not too sweet and the variety of drinks is phenomenal. I ve been back more than three times already!

Such a cute shop, and fun concept. And the gourmet drink and cake are so tasty!! I completely recommend trying the kiwi lemonade! Its refreshing
Had the Pandan Pineapple Coconut Cake with Fresh Kiwi Lemonade and I loved it! Probably will order less sweet for the drink next time.
very cute little dessert place in the neighborhood! very interesting concept and beautiful presentation!
Have ordered birthday cake from them twice, and loved the look and loved the taste.  Also enjoyed their dessert cup + drink combo.  Very neat!
Hai we celebrate our daughter birthday this month cake was fantastic everyone loved it my small suggestion is to add more flavours and more design please and thank you
Innovative design for combining cake and drink . I had cake#8 + drink#8, taste great, will definitely come back to try others!
The girls are super sweet and the cakes are freaking amazing!!!! The earl grey latte and toasted rice cake are to die for.

I tried the short cake with iced americano and raspberry lemon cake with iced americano. Pretty damn good.
Although it is pricy, it is worth every penny. I have been there twice, and they did not disappoint me.
